# SaaS kit: protect proven structure

This app was scaffolded with `@llanesleonardo/create-saas` and pins `@llanesleonardo/saas-platform` + `@llanesleonardo/saas-product-shell`. That stack is a **proven** dual-mode kit. Do not silently break it.

## Time split (default)

| Focus | ~Effort |
|-------|---------|
| **Domain** (`/product/*`, `src/domain/`, product APIs) | **~90%** |
| Platform / shell / scaffold structure | **~10%**, only after ask / explicit OK |

SaaS feature upgrades happen in the **package repos**, then pin bumps — not by rewriting kits inside this app.

## Ask or recommend first

Before changing any of the following, **stop**: recommend (what / why / risk) and **ask for confirmation** unless the user already ordered that exact change.

- Proxy gates (`requireFirstAdmin`, `requireWorkspace`, public paths)
- `AppShellNav`, theme, workspace switcher, default Workspace/Account nav
- Auth / setup / Log In / first-admin flow
- Tenancy handlers, workspace cookies, onboarding
- Billing dual-mode (saas checkout vs selfhosted matrix + invoices)
- Package pins (`saas-platform`, `saas-product-shell`)
- Forking or replacing shell UI kits with one-off copies

**OK without asking:** domain UI under Product placeholders, branding, domain APIs/schemas, wiring product hooks (`onWorkspaceCreated`), domain bugfixes.

## Do / Don’t

- **Do** extend Product section + domain code; consume `@llanesleonardo/saas-product-shell/ui` and route kits
- **Don’t** gut dual-mode tenancy, billing, or sidebar “to improve” it in-app
- Gap in the kit → recommend package change + `npx @llanesleonardo/create-saas update-pins`
